rComments: Had her for Physics 2 online in French. I personally find physics hard so the class was going to be tough regardless - but content aside, this prof genuinely cares about the understanding of her students and will go over any examples/ re explain concepts with no problem when asked. She also answers emails fairly fast.

Class in french. Explained her PowerPoint really well and does examples live. Annotates during class to help you understand. Answers all questions even if she has to repeat herself. Asks questions and expects participation. Graded homework that reflected what was on the exams. Midterms are very easy if you complete all the hw and DGDs.

Professor Sebbani is very subpar when it comes to explanations. She simply reads the slides and it is very difficult to take much knowledge from her courses and apply it to the assignments. Luckily, I had a python base so it was a lot easier for me but anyone who does not have a coding base will have a tough time. Also, the TAs are garbage.
Horrible prof
Shes the worst the teacher Ive ever had
Prof reads from the slides and repeats the same answer to a question when asked twice . Explanations don t match the level of difficulty in the exams . But she s a really nice and genuine person .

Professor Sebbani is a pretty average prof, but good god she needs to put some of her TAs on a leash. Bunch of narcissistic dingdongs whose only talent is their ability to carry the weight of their God complexes.
WOULD NOT RECOMMEND ANYONE TO TAKE THIS CLASS
absolutely horrible, does not answer questions, not caring, explains things badly

This might be the worst programming introduction I've ever seen for sure. Explains concepts in a wordy and confusing manner. Rarely uses live coding. Extremly confusing exams/homework that have to be re-read multiple times. Her class notes are mediocre at best. Refuses to setup teams correctly and keeps getting muted in class.
No

le professeur connais la programmation java mais ne sais pas transmettre. elle ne prend pas le temps de bien écouter la question qu'elle crie et reprend les meme explications au lieu d'écouter et bien cerner le problème de l'élève. Je me suis ensorti avec mes propres efforts et recherche. J'arrivais meme pas à suivre son cours. prenez un autre prof

I attended her class for the first couple of sessions and switched into the english section. She did not seem to know how to teach, she was disorganized and didn't post the lectures properly so I missed the first one. Students would ask simple questions and she did not know how to answer them. Avoid for programming classes.

Nah man avoid at all costs. Literally makes java more complicated than it should be. Worst prof I've had in my first year of uni by far. She says: Don't hesitate to send me emails. Yet she won't even try to help you out. She'll answer them in the laziest way possible.

Her lectures are not organized and she keeps contradicting herself. Test are hard and her test is mainly based off of one lecture when the test was supposed to cover 7 lecture, the lecture she said that wasn't important was the highlight of the test. She also d'ont responds to email. Avoid this prof at all cost if you can!

Ignores emails. Classes are unorganized. Multiple Brightspace classes. Teaches Java with slides instead of an IDE. She says "it's the same thing". Her code is ugly and wrong. Students keep kicking others out and muting the prof in Teams but she keeps saying "that's just MS Teams, it's broken" instead of acknowledging the problem.

Unorganized. Disrespectful. Useless. Created 6 BS tabs when only 1 was needed. Each student had 2 of 6 tabs. Some had their BS class updated, others have nothing. Multiple MS Teams links. Host permission granted to everyone. Screamed at us, said it was not her problem. "Go contact tech help yourself". ENGLISH textbook. Taught Java with SLIDES!!!

She's definitely not the best but not the worst prof. Even though her lectures were quite boring and made up of just powerpoint slides, her tests are extremely hard (you can easily fail but just doing 5-6 questions wrong) and the online labs were nothing but waste of time, she helps her students to succeed and responds to emails lightning fast.

Prof Sebbani clearly loves physics and cares for her students, however, she is not the best at teaching. PHY 2361 is very abstract and it was unfortunate to have a teacher that couldn't explain properly. Avoid this teacher if you don't want to teach yourself Introductory Quantum Mech or Special Relativity. Otherwise, you're in for a treat.
Nice prof, would recommend for sure in the futur
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Two words: awesome prof! Wants you to succeed but you have to work HARD for it. Easy A.

This teacher saved my life. I used to think physics was a horrible class meant to be hard and so I dropped it and took it with her in the summer. I also took physics 2 with her in the winter and thanks to her I actually like physics now.

I would not recommend taking a class with her. She is very nice, but her lectures involve her reading off the slides and it's impossible to understand anything she is saying. The midterms AND the final exam are only around TEN multiple choice questions so it's easy to get a bad grade in her class if you only screw up a few questions

Avoid at all cost! She doesn't know what she is teaching just basically reading off of her slides. Her creativity is whack. Confuses the class 24/7. Make sure to get the textbook cause you'll not survive with her way of teaching unless you're super smart like that one guy in our class who keeps his jacket on everytime and answers all the questions.

Poor prof. If you want a chance to a good grade in here class, learn the material on your own. All she does show the mathematics behind certain equations and read of her slides. You can never guess how her exams are going to turn out, as she is completely unclear about everything. I'm not the only one when I say avoid at all costs...

Elle ne fait que copier ce qu'elle a déjà écrit sur les slides, elle ne fait que les lire. on ne comprend rien a ces cours, vous devez travaillez seul, midterm facile, final infaisable, durs dans la correction, médiocre, .

Physics is not my thing so I found this course very hard, but also the prof was not very clear with the material. I found the lectures quite boring which made me want to skip, but I would recommend going to the class. There was only one midterm and a final and weekly homework assignment (do those they are easy marks).

Un cours qui pourrais être super intéressant mais la prof reste dans sa zone de confort et elle fait seulement des calculs mathématiques même si le cours demande aucun préalable en maths... Ses explications sont très brèves et sont appris mots pour mots de ses diapositives. En plus, ses diapos sont traduit mots pour mots du textbook anglais.
